[1mNAME[0m
       taiclockd - announce the system's clock through TAICLOCK

[1mSYNOPSIS[0m
       [1mtaiclockd[0m

[1mDESCRIPTION[0m
       [1mtaiclockd [22mannounces the local UNIX clock through the TAICLOCK protocol.
       It listens for TAICLOCK requests through UDP and responds with the sys-
       tem's current time.

       [1mDO   NOT  RUN  taiclockd  IF  YOUR  SYSTEM  IS  TUNED  BY  xntpd.   [22mSee
       [1mhttp://pobox.com/~djb/proto/utctai.html [22mfor further discussion.

       [1mtaiclockd [22mdoes not need to run as root.

